														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4839492">
									

<p>so there's a module at the top that defines the <span>for SHADOW text and then you just signify which of then words you want in that span. It's not that complicated but I get that looking at the thing is a mess in just code:</span></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><span><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></span></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><span><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></span></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<hr />
<p><span><strong>post this at the top:</strong><br />
[[module css]]<br />
@import url('<a href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Ruslan+Display">https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Ruslan+Display</a>');<br />
.shadow {<br />
font-family: 'Ruslan Display', cursive;<br />
font-size: 110%;<br />
}</span></p>
<p><span>[[/module]]</span></p>
<p><span><strong>and then this for whatever you want the text to change:</strong></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p><span>[[span class=&quot;shadow&quot;]]Specter talking here.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>et voila!</p>
<hr /></div>
</div>
</div>
<p>So Specter is certainly coming back with the rest, and he's one of my favs as well :) (I wish I could take credit for his creation, but the only characters we created for this was Lucretia and Carlotta)</p>
<p>Stay tuned, we'll be bringing out the sequel series soonish</p>

